node.title: ACT fully vaccinates 95 per cent of eligible population, records 13 new cases
node.alt: A nurse in a face mask pulls vaccine out of a vial.
node.description: The ACT records 13 new cases of COVID-19 as it becomes the first Australian jurisdiction to fully vaccinate 95 per cent of its eligible population.
node.content: ["The ACT has recorded 13\u00a0new\u00a0COVID-19 cases, as the territory becomes the first Australian jurisdiction to fully vaccinate 95 per cent of its eligible\u00a0population.\u00a0", "There is currently one person in hospital with the virus. They are in intensive care and require ventilation.\u00a0", "There are 135\u00a0active cases of COVID-19 in the territory.", "Ninety-five per cent of eligible Canberrans aged 12 and older have now received two doses of a COVID-19 vaccine, though the official record will not be updated until tomorrow.", "The ACT is the first Australian state or territory to reach the milestone.\u00a0", "The ACT government had\u00a0repeatedly said the territory was on track to be one of the world's most vaccinated jurisdictions, with double-dose vaccination rates expected to reach more than 99 per cent by Christmas.", "More to come.\u00a0"]
